-- Obama to Discuss Military Sexual Assaults With Joint Chiefs
-- B y   R o g e r   R u n n i n g e n
-- 2013-05-16T14:36:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-16/obama-to-discuss-military-sexual-assaults-with-joint-chiefs.html
President  Barack Obama  will meet this
afternoon with Defense Secretary Chuck Hagel and the Joint
Chiefs of Staff to discuss how to curb sexual assaults in the
U.S. military.  The meeting comes as the armed forces are being confronted
with what Army General Martin Dempsey, chairman of the Joint
Chiefs, has called “a crisis” for the military.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Roger Runningen in Washington at 
 rrunningen@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
